news.title: K Raheja Corp buys B R Chopra's bungalow in Mumbai for nearly Rs 183 crore
news.para: The developer has acquired the property from Renu Ravi Chopra, wife of Ravi Chopra and daughter in law of B.R. Chopra, who is known for several blockbuster films including Waqt, Naya Daur, The Burning Train and Nikaah apart from one of the most successful serials in Indian television history, Mahabharat.

news.title: Signature Global to invest Rs 550 crore to build housing project in Gurugram
news.para: The total project cost is Rs 550 crore for the second phase, the company said, adding that the independent floors would be sold in a price range of Rs 62-72 lakh.

news.title: Gurugram: Pipes finally reach homes, yet water won't flow
news.para: According to officials, just 45 societies of the sectors that are lined along the Dwarka Expressway and the Southern Peripheral Road have taken individual water connections despite the GMDA having installed 93km of the 119km master pipeline.

news.title: Maharashtra's first integrated township in KDMC to get 66% property tax relief
news.para: While the township's Palava City Management Association (PCMA) has been charging residents for providing basic amentities and infrastructure, residents have also been paying taxes for the same to the KDMC.

news.title: Gujarat HC stays eviction of slum dwellers from riverbed in Rajkot for a day
news.para: Petitioner’s advocate Aftab Ansari requested the high court for an urgent hearing claiming that the civic authorities would come for demolition on Tuesday morning and the residents have been given a very short notice for eviction.

news.title: Kerala: GCDA housing project to miss yet another deadline
news.para: The project, which had already missed multiple deadlines, was scheduled to be completed on June 15 but it has been rescheduled to July 31.

news.title: Ludhiana: Watch draw of lots for Atal apartments scheme online
news.para: Deputy commissioner Surabhi Malik on Monday reviewed final arrangements for Ludhiana Improvement Trust’s draw of lots for 336 high-income-group (HIG) and 240 middle-income-group (MIG) flats under the Atal Apartment Scheme.

news.title: About 20,000 housing societies in Maharashtra can gain from cooperative bank funding
news.para: The housing finance limit of 5% of the total asset is expected to boost self-development of societies in Pune, Mumbai, and Thane, Maharashtra Housing Federation vice-chairman Suhas Patwardhan said.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP bans sale and purchase of properties in Sushant Lok-2
news.para: Batth further said the department has also written to the revenue department not to execute any sale deed registration of any property situated in the township and update the revenue records as well.

news.title: Gurugram: No help from RWAs, survey of illegal colonies hits hurdle
news.para: The MCG in April had constituted ward-wise teams, comprising junior engineers and patwaris, to start survey of unauthorised residential colonies falling under the civic body’s jurisdiction.

news.title: Embassy REIT distributes over Rs 5,800 crore to unitholders since listing
news.para: In the last three years, the company has leased 6.4 million sq ft across 135 deals, delivered 2.5 million sq ft of new space and grew unitholder base by 10x to over 40,000.

news.title: Infra.market raises $50 million from Liquidity Group's Mars Unicorn Fund
news.para: The latest fundraise by Infra.market, which was valued at USD 2.5 billion at its last fundraise in August 2021, comes after reports of non-disclosure of over Rs 200 crore in income and investigations by the Income Tax authorities earlier this year.

news.title: Pune-based ABIL group's founder challenges his arrest by CBI
news.para: Bhosale was arrested by CBI in May last month in connection with its probe in the Yes bank-DHFL scam. Bhosale who is under judicial custody is lodged at Arthur jail after the special court, CBI rejected the remand application of CBI seeking further custody for five days.

news.title: UK builder Countryside puts itself up for sale as shareholder pressure mounts
news.para: The company said its third-largest shareholder In-Cap will participate in the formal sale process, and it is currently not in talks with any other potential suitor. Countryside in late May rejected In-Cap's 295-pence a share proposal as it "undervalued" the company.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Pipeline work done, Siddharth Vihar to get Ganga water this year
news.para: UP housing board’s upcoming Siddharth Vihar township will get Ganga jal water supply by the end of this year. Currently, Ganga jal, which is high in demand because of its potable quality, is supplied to a few townships only, most in trans-Hindon areas.
